25|$|In 1979, Laaksonen with {{businessman}} and friend Durk Dehner co-founded the Tom of Finland Company, and in 1984 established the Tom of Finland Foundation dedicated to collecting, preserving, and exhibiting homoerotic artwork. Although Laaksonen was quite successful at this point, with his biography on <b>the</b> <b>best-seller</b> list, and Benedikt Taschen, the world's largest art book publisher reprinting and expanding a monograph of his works, {{he was most}} proud of the Foundation. The scope of the organization expanded to erotic works of all types, sponsored contests, exhibits, and started {{the groundwork for a}} museum of erotic art.|$|E
